			<div class="comment-body"><p>They way I see &#8216;setting up&#8217; projects in both applications is that in FCP it resolves around the material you&#8217;ve got imported, and in AVID it&#8217;s the actual project you create. What I love in AVID is that you just have to worry about setting up the project&#8217;s frame rate correctly and after that always being able to switch between HD/SD or corresponding framerates (like 25 of 50 frames here in PAL-country). Want to export your timeline in SD? no problem, want to export the same timeline as HD, no problem. You&#8217;re not really &#8216;setting up&#8217; that much, because every option is still (and always) on the table.</p>
</div>

